{"id": "EUVD-2018-4210", "enisaUuid": "fc69f4b2-ba5e-30af-a6e4-1a43479387d7", "description": "In net/socket.c in the Linux kernel through 4.17.1, there is a race condition between fchownat and close in cases where they target the same socket file descriptor, related to the sock_close and sockfs_setattr functions. fchownat does not increment the file descriptor reference count, which allows close to set the socket to NULL during fchownat's execution, leading to a NULL pointer dereference and system crash.", "datePublished": "2018-06-12T12:00:00", "dateUpdated": "2024-08-05T08:30:59", "baseScore": 5.9, "baseScoreVersion": "3.0", "baseScoreVector": "CVSS:3.0/AV:N/AC:H/PR:N/UI:N/S:U/C:N/I:N/A:H", "references": ["https://www.suse.com/security/cve/CVE-2018-12232.html", "https://access.redhat.com/errata/RHSA-2018:2948", "https://ubuntu.com/security/CVE-2018-12232", "https://alas.aws.amazon.com/cve/html/CVE-2018-12232.html", "https://usn.ubuntu.com/3752-2/", "https://usn.ubuntu.com/3752-3/", "http://git.kernel.org/cgit/linux/kernel/git/torvalds/linux.git/commit/?id=6d8c50dcb029872b298eea68cc6209c866fd3e14", "https://patchwork.ozlabs.org/patch/926519/", "https://lkml.org/lkml/2018/6/5/14", "http://www.securityfocus.com/bid/104453", "https://usn.ubuntu.com/3752-1/", "https://github.com/torvalds/linux/commit/6d8c50dcb029872b298eea68cc6209c866fd3e14"], "aliases": ["CVE-2018-12232"], "assigner": "mitre", "epss": 3.3, "enisaIdProduct": [{"id": "b8cdde53-c878-314b-a251-0ce0a980848d", "product": {"name": "n/a"}, "product_version": "n/a"}], "enisaIdVendor": [{"id": "4e1bf6fa-a482-3241-8979-da3cf2a5f8a3", "vendor": {"name": "n/a"}}], "isExploited": false}